    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-17T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-17T17:00:00-05:00" n="341"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d341">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/360</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-17T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 17, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7783. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 503. Embassy’s 10002, May 10 [<hi rend="italic">11</hi>], 5 p.m. Your 561.
                    Referring to four mentioned Swedish steamers we feel that all four of these
                    boats should call at a United States port on the way to South America to carry
                    either coal or general cargo at our option, then the balance of the program
                    suggested by you would be approved. For your information there is a great
                    shortage of tonnage from here to South America just now and we feel this is an
                    important condition that they should agree to. This shortage is caused by
                    removal of South American liners by Allied Governments for use in transatlantic
                    service.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
